      "name": "Experimental hemolysis index comparison — FDA pump benchmark",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values compared against published FDA benchmark experimental data across all five flow-speed operating points. Mean absolute relative error is 8.2% across operating points, within the acceptance criterion of 15%. Turbulence model sensitivity study (k-omega SST vs. k-epsilon realizable) shows less than 4% variation in NIH predictions. Lagrangian particle tracking used for stress accumulation along representative blood element trajectories.",
